-- Taiwan Stocks: Astro, E Ink Holdings, International Games, HTC
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-07-09T05:49:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/taiwan-stocks-astro-e-ink-holdings-international-games-htc.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  fell 0.8 percent to 7,309.96, the biggest
drop since June 8.  Gaming companies:  Astro Corp. (3064)  (3064 TT), which markets
motherboards and software for commercial arcade game machines,
climbed 1.1 percent to NT$45, the highest close since May 15.
 International Games System Co. (3293)  (3293 TT) advanced 1.5 percent to
NT$135. Residents of Taiwan’s Matsu islands voted in favor of
casinos to help attract tourists.  E Ink Holdings Inc. (8069 TT) tumbled 7 percent to NT$32.1,
the biggest drop since Dec. 6. The supplier to Amazon.com Inc.’s
Kindle said June sales slumped 71 percent from a year earlier to
NT$532.5 million ($17.8 million), according to a statement.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT), Asia’s second-largest smartphone
maker, retreated 5.6 percent to NT$304, the lowest close since
March 15, 2010. Second-quarter net income declined 58 percent
from a year earlier to NT$7.4 billion, HTC said in a statement
on its website on July 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
